PRACTICAL NO 8: 
Aim: Write a Student class with three properties. The useBean action declares a 
JavaBean for use in a JSP. Write Java Application to access JavaBeans Properties. 
Step 1: Create a java web application --> Create JSP files --> Expand your project -
> Right click on Web Pages folder --> Select JSP file --> Give name of the file and 
click on finish.
Step 2: Create 1 java class file and import getters and setters in it. StudentBean.java
package bean; 
public class StudentBean { 
 private String course; 
 public String getCourse() { 
 return course; 
 } 
 public void setCourse(String course) { 
 this.course = course; 
 } 
 private String lastname; 
 public String getLastname() { 
 return lastname; 
 } 
 public void setLastname(String lastname) { 
 this.lastname = lastname; 
 } 
 private String firstname; 
 public String getFirstname() { 
 return firstname; 
 } 
 public void setFirstname(String firstname) { 
 this.firstname = firstname; 
 } 
 
} 
Step 3: Create 2 JSP files, 1 html and write code inside it.
